name: Acetaminophen
description: A non-narcotic analgesic that relieves pain and reduces fever. It belongs to the category of nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs). The usual adult dosage is 325 to 650 mg every 4 to 6 hours, not exceeding 4 g per day

name: Amoxicillin
description: A penicillin antibiotic that treats bacterial infections such as ear infections, pneumonia, urinary tract infections and strep throat. It belongs to the category of beta-lactam antibiotics. The usual adult dosage is 250 to 500 mg every 8 hours or 500 to 875 mg every 12 hours, depending on the type and severity of infection.

name: Atorvastatin
description: A statin drug that lowers cholesterol and triglycerides in the blood and reduces the risk of heart attack, stroke and other cardiovascular problems. It belongs to the category of HMG-CoA reductase inhibitors. The usual adult dosage is 10 to 80 mg once daily, depending on the level of cholesterol and other factors

name: Citalopram
description: A selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) that treats depression and anxiety disorders. It belongs to the category of antidepressants. The usual adult dosage is 20 mg once daily, which may be increased to a maximum of 40 mg per day after at least one week

name: Lisinopril
description: An angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitor that lowers blood pressure and treats heart failure and kidney problems. It belongs to the category of antihypertensives. The usual adult dosage is 10 to 40 mg once daily, depending on the condition being treated

name: Trazodone
description: A serotonin antagonist and reuptake inhibitor (SARI) that treats depression and insomnia. It belongs to the category of antidepressants. The usual adult dosage is 150 to 600 mg per day in one or more divided doses, depending on the response and tolerance
